CDB Reader / Cretor for ruby
============================

Author: Markus Schirp <mbj@seonic.net>
License: Ruby's License

Description:

Simple CDB reading an writing Plugin for Ruby.

Constant - Database Reference: 

  http://cr.yp.to/cdb.html
 

Requirements:
=============

CDB from DJB or TinyCDB:

  LDFLAGS for cdb:
    -l:cdb.a -l:unix.a -l:buffer.a -l:byte -l:alloc
  INCLUDES for cdb:
    cdb.h
    cdb_make.h

  LDFLAG for thinycdb:
    -lcdb
  INCLUDES for tinycdb:
    cdb.h

Gentoo Package Names

CDB: dev-db/cdb
TinyCDB: dev-db/tinycdb

Examples:
=========

reading:

require 'cdb'

File.open("some.cdb") do |file|
  reader = CDB::CDBReader.new(file)
  reader.each_value("somekey") do |value|
    # do something with value
  end
end

writing:

require 'cdb'

File.open("some.cdb","w") do |file|
  CDB::CDBMaker.fill(file) do |maker|
    (1..10).each do |x|
      key = "key#{x}"
      1.upto(x) do |y|
        value = "value#{x}.#{y}"
        maker.store(key,value)
      end
    end
  end
end
